    "comment": "Rationale: Fig. 8; MAGI3 is concentrated on IPL sublaminae 2 and 4 were cone bipolar axons made synapses onto amacrine or ganglion dendrites. Hovewer the images do not tell us if MAGI3 is a presynaptic or a postsynaptic protein. The data only indicate that MAGI3 is a \"synaptic\" protein.\n\nLiteral\n\"Double-label immunohistochemistry revealed that MAGI-2 and MAGI-3-rich\nsublaminae are nonoverlapping, indicating that MAGI-2 and MAGI-3 are present in distinct synapses.Confocal images suggested that MAGI-2 and Sidekick-2 were present in the same synaptic puncta, as were MAGI-3 and Dscam (Fig. 8b,c,)\". Experimental description: Literal from M&M\n\"Retinal cells were dissociated from embryonic chicks at E16.\"",
